Ask HN: Is your current data management solution working well for you?
text:
I'm curious about how well your data management solution fits your workflow.

On 3 occasions, my former employer "wasted" hundreds of thousands of dollars procuring data management software but we ended up only using about 10% of the features in each instance. It took them a while to even start thinking of getting a custom-built solution.

Do you find that you are facing the same degree of inefficiency with your current data management work?

In other words, does you current data management software stack have way more features than you will ever need? How do you deal with that situation?

title: Ask HN: Resources for New Async Teams?
text:
I’m working with a couple of collaborators and we’re about to launch a new app. We work entirely async/distributed with no meetings, a bit like an OSS project.

Are there any examples of for-profit companies that work this way (async/remote first) that we could look to for guidance or inspiration? Any blogs, books, etc. that cover this topic? Anyone had success with this model and has wisdom to share?

Most of what I find online is resources helping larger orgs transition to remote. The best I’ve found is 37signals.com and Twist’s blog https://twist.com/remote-work-guides
